cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper addresses the problem of depth estimation from a single still image using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a deep model that fuses information from multiple CNN side outputs using continuous Conditional Random Fields (CRFs), which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed model is designed to work with monocular depth estimation, which is a subfield of robotics and autonomous systems. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.RO (Robotics).
